<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-53-0894 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper describes non-linear numerical simulations of ideal internalkink modes in cylindrical geometry with a flat central q-profile as amodel for the rapid sawtooth collapse seen in large tokamaks. The resultingplasma motion is consistent with that obtained experimentally from X-raytomographic reconstruction. Attention is drawn to the effects of limitedpoloidal resolution in this diagnostic. (author). 18 refs, 11 figs.</TEXT></DOC>